{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Gv1i9ZA8uGn68su4akq2dd","type":"tool_result","content":"9:  - ``_parse_ruledout_line`` recognizes leading-position ``[RULEDOUT]``\n11:  - ``_attach_ruledout`` resolves the attachment target for a RULEDOUT\n14:    parse-then-attach composition test confirms multiple RULEDOUT\n16:  - ``_DEPS_RE`` recognizes ``@deps`` sibling lines, captures indent\n19:  - ``_attach_deps`` resolves the attachment target for an ``@deps``\n24:    to confirm a deeply-indented ``@deps`` lands on a nested subtask.\n123:        rec = _parse_ruledout_line(\"  [RULEDOUT] tried restart\", 5)\n130:        rec = _parse_ruledout_line(\"[RULEDOUT] orphan approach\", 1)\n133:        assert rec.text == \"orphan approach\"\n136:        rec = _parse_ruledout_line(\"    [RULEDOUT]\", 9)\n142:        rec = _parse_ruledout_line(\"  [RULEDOUT] foo   \", 3)\n147:        # A RULEDOUT token that appears mid-line is prose, not a\n148:        # RULEDOUT line. Only the leading-position form is recognized.\n149:        assert _parse_ruledout_line(\"- [ ] talk about [RULEDOUT] later\", 1) is None\n152:        # `startswith(\"[RULEDOUT]\")` semantics: the bracket must close\n154:        assert _parse_ruledout_line(\"[RULEDOUT_OTHER] foo\", 1) is None\n167:        # RULEDOUT at indent 4 sits as a sibling under `child`\n182:        # A column-0 RULEDOUT after the stack has been popped (e.g.\n191:        # A stray [RULEDOUT] before any task in the phase has nothing\n192:        # to attach to; the caller is expected to drop it.\n202:        # parse each [RULEDOUT] line, route it to its parent via\n204:        # sibling RULEDOUTs at the child indent must all land on the\n212:            (\"    [RULEDOUT] first approach\", 10),\n213:            (\"    [RULEDOUT] second approach\", 11),\n214:            (\"    [RULEDOUT] third approach\", 12),\n235:        m = _DEPS_RE.match(\"@deps T-000001\")\n241:        m = _DEPS_RE.match(\"@deps T-000001 T-000002 T-000003\")\n247:        m = _DEPS_RE.match(\"    @deps T-000001 T-000002\")\n254:        m = _DEPS_RE.match(\"@deps T-000001    T-000002\")\n264:            \"@deps\",\n265:            \"@deps \",\n266:            \" @deps_ T-000001\",\n275:        # Canonical form: @deps is indented strictly more than the\n284:        # \"Forgot to indent\" form: @deps at the same indent as its\n311:        # The most recent task is more indented than @deps, so it is\n321:        # A @deps line before any task in scope has nothing to attach\n322:        # to — the caller is expected to drop it. No root-task fallback\n337:        # Compose _DEPS_RE with _attach_deps: a deeply-indented @deps\n346:        m = _DEPS_RE.match(\"      @deps T-000001 T-000002\")\n528:    stack at phase/subsection/bugs boundaries, and dispatching ``@deps``\n529:    and ``[RULEDOUT]`` siblings to the parent task. Tests below\n567:        # that follow have no enclosing phase and are dropped.\n568:        text = \"## Phase phase_001: Core\\n- [ ] orphan task\\n\"\n665:            \"  [RULEDOUT] tried restart\\n\"\n666:            \"  [RULEDOUT] tried reinstall\\n\"\n680:            \"  @deps T-000001\\n\"\n692:            \"    [RULEDOUT] tried polling\\n\"\n694:            \"    @deps T-000002\\n\"\n719:    def test_tasks_before_any_section_are_dropped_in_compat_mode(self) -> None:\n721:        # an orphan. Compat mode drops silently; strict mode (2.5.4)\n724:        plan = parse_plan(\"- [ ] orphan\\n## Stage 1: Core\\n- [ ] real\\n\")\n820:    def test_lines_before_h1_are_dropped(self) -> None:\n821:        # Outside any active prose region, prose is dropped — matches the\n828:    def test_prose_after_first_task_in_phase_is_dropped(self) -> None:\n831:        # accumulator and are dropped in compat mode."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9a449ac0-394d-4684-a780-cf9347c419c5","uuid":"290d990a-f529-4d54-8c75-6f2abe334715","timestamp":"2026-05-16T02:59:49.980Z","tool_use_result":{"mode":"cont