{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_013mZ4r2tddrt9EoxVmB5jvF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have enough context now. The task is to wire syntax-error reporting into compat mode. The clearest case currently silently dropped: a `@deps` line with no task to attach to (the docstring already calls it \"malformed input\"). Let me also raise on a `[RULEDOUT]` line with truly no target (no fallback root either).\n\nLet me think about scope. The existing test at line 719 documents that orphan TASKS stay dropped in compat mode (matching mcloop). Orphan `@deps` is the right case to raise — mcloop never recognized `@deps` at all, so there's no compat history to preserve, and it's documented as malformed input."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1254,"cache_read_input_tokens":84635,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1254},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9a449ac0-394d-4684-a780-cf9347c419c5","uuid":"f41250b8-ced3-4de5-8432-0af043aade2d"}
