{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01VGGVc8VJVhQGcNX8vHadNC","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01ApKgTkWRd1Q9ojr2hs8rdv","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/mhcoen/proj/bob-tools/NOTES.md","old_string":"## Hypotheses","new_string":"- 2026-05-15 [2.5.4] Compat-mode syntax errors are scoped narrowly. The\n  task description says \"raise PlanSyntaxError on syntax violations in\n  compat mode\", but most of the candidates (orphan tasks, prose outside\n  accumulators, `### subsection` inside Bugs) have established mcloop\n  precedent for being silently tolerated and so stay dropped in compat\n  mode (deferred to strict mode in Stage 3, per the 2.5.2 NOTES entry).\n  The one case that does raise in compat mode is an orphan `@deps` line\n  with no preceding task to attach to: `@deps` is a planfile-introduced\n  feature with no mcloop history, so there is no compat behavior to\n  preserve, and the keyword has no semantic interpretation absent a\n  target task. The `_raise_syntax_error` helper centralizes the\n  message-quoting convention (backticks around the offending line) so\n  Stage 3's strict-mode call sites can reuse the same format.\n\n## Hypotheses"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":431,"cache_read_input_tokens":102518,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":431},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9a449ac0-394d-4684-a780-cf9347c419c5","uuid":"50fbdf44-fef5-4150-b3f8-fafde7fb7487"}
